h2 Want to give it a try?

p.
  Jamrock is available through a custom installer,
  it downloads the package and uncompress it locally at your #[code $HOME], e.g.

pre.hljs: code.
  curl -L get.jamrock.dev | bash
  jamrock init my-app
  cd my-app
  ./bin/node --version
  ./bin/node serve --watch --nofswatch

p Once started you should get something like this:

pre.hljs: code.
  â–  Jamrock v#{pkg.version} (node #{process.version}, ?)
  Processing ./pages to ./build
  Listening on #[a(href='http://localhost:8080' target='_blank') http://localhost:8080]

p.
  Open that URL in your browser and enjoy!

